nodes.text: Level 1671 was a level of the ecumenopolis that covered the entire surface of the planet Coruscant. It was 3,456 levels from the planet's surface on Level 5127. One night in 7951 C.R.C., the Pau'an criminal Zodu Onglo made an attempt to sell a cache of stolen weapons on Level 1671, but botched the sale and ended up being apprehended by the Coruscant Security Force's underworld police for aggravated assault. The Security Force's Inspector Tanivos Divo questioned a Twi'lek witness next to a smoking corpse as Onglo was led away in stuncuffs.
Level 1671 was first mentioned in the 2018 reference book Star Wars: Scum and Villainy: Case Files on the Galaxy's Most Notorious, which was written by Pablo Hidalgo.
